My sister has lived in Hurst and Euless in recent years -- we've visited them in both locales as well as their current address, so I'm getting somewhat familiar with the area.

Is there a Sunflower Market in the area, or Wild Oats or even Whole Foodes (tho they're both kinda spendy). We'll need more slavored soy milk, hormone-free dairy milk and organic vegies than I can pack for the drive, and it's not the kind of stuff Sunny (my sis) keeps on hand, nor do i expect she would know where to find such fare.

Syl

messages.msgSnippet: Well, we aren t very far from our last move.  Still in the DFW area.  Our last house was a literal house of horrors. We re still unschooling, hubby still
messages.messageBody:
Well, we aren't very far from our last move. Still in the DFW area. Our
last house was a literal house of horrors.

We're still unschooling, hubby still travels ALL the time. No new babies.
;) And we are now without a car. :( Otherwise all is well!

I just overloaded after our move and once things began to fall apart in our
last house, it took everything I had to keep up. We're doing well now.
Nice house, smaller but planned much better. I'm not sure when we'll ever
make it up to Michigan now. Hell, I can barely make it to the grocery
store! LOL

I see I came back during a little storm here, but I'll try to hold my tongue
and let everyone get used to my big mouth again. <beg>

Glad to be back!

Jen

this group but things are settling down and I'm going to attempt to jump
back in. When I left last we were moving and have since moved again,
hopefully permanently this time. (Long rediculous story there.)

Next weekend is the Rethinking Education conference in Irving, Tx and
Haleigh and I are going. I was wondering if anyone here is going or has
ever been???

Anyway, guess that's all for now. Hi everyone!!!! :)

Jennifer

and Chloe
